Hi Stephen.
 >> Is there a good list of changes / new features in upcoming 2.4
 >> kernel release?
 > You can be sure there will be once 2.4 is released!
 >> 	- Will 2.4 have 2(4)+GB filesize support on 32bit machines?
 > Yes.
 >> 	- Will 2.4 have 32bit uid/gid support?
 > Yes.
 >> 	- Will 2.4 have Nfsv3 support?
 > Yes.   
 > All of these are already in 2.3, and ext2 has the large file and
 > large uid support enabled in 2.3 (with appropriate compatibility
 > checks to prevent things going bad when you mix old and new
 > kernels).
Can I add one to that list:
 Q. Is there any likelihood of the e2fs-compressed patch (or anything
    similar) making its way into the standard kernel any time soon?
Early 2.4 will do fine, but 2.2 would be even better...
Best wishes from Riley.
